headline: 'The Five' on Canada Truckers, vaccine mandates

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.sentences: Home invasions --

utterances.speaker: JESSE WATTERS, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: Hello, everyone. I'm Jesse Watters along with Judge Jeanine Pirro, Geraldo Rivera, Dagen McDowell, and Greg Gutfeld. It's five o'clock in New York City, and this is THE FIVE. Joe Biden looking to crush the trucker protests in Canada before it spreads here. The president telling Justin Trudeau to get tough and cracked down on the freedom convoy. And White House officials are urging Canadian leaders to use their federal powers to break up the protests. It looks like they got the message. Ontario, declaring a state of emergency, and is demanding the truckers go home now. And Justin Trudeau issuing this direct threat.

utterances.speaker: JUSTIN TRUDEAU, PRIME MINISTER OF CANADA
utterances.sentences: We talked about the U.S. base flooding of the 911 phone lines in Ottawa, the presence of U.S. citizens in the blockades, and the impact of foreign money to fund this illegal activity. Everything is on the table, because this unlawful activity has to end, and it will end.

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.sentences: Some of the organizers of these protesters -- which as I mentioned, started more than a week ago. They do want to overthrow the government.

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.sentences: The police chief says COVID protests are a, quote, "nationwide insurrection driven by madness."

utterances.speaker: BRIANNA KEILAR, CNN, ANCHOR
utterances.sentences: A nationwide insurrection driven by madness.

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.sentences: It's not just truckers. There's a lot of, I've heard there's QAnon supporters in the crowd.

utterances.speaker: PAULA NEWTON, CNN CORRESPONDENT
utterances.sentences: Residents that I have spoken to who say they feel terrorized, intimidated.

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.sentences: Look at them --

utterances.speaker: GREG GUTFELD, FOX NEWS CO-HOST
utterances.sentences: You know what, I like the sound of that, and I like the look of that map. You know, when Justin Trudeau said everything is on the table, didn't he just suggest a willingness to go to war? Because they are saying that Americans are involved, so did he just basically say let's go, America? I find that very odd. Look, we saw this coming. When this first started, we, that it was going to be called an insurrection on 16 wheels, this is the same demonization that the media did with Trump voters, with parents at school board meetings. Everybody becomes a Nazi because they can't argue with them. The first thing they do is they try the blanket smear. I mean, do you really think these are the type of people that are going to mess with the Super Bowl? These are the people who watch the Super Bowl. And it's disgusting that our White House is putting them on par with terrorists. I can't even name a Canadian terrorist. I can name a lot of terrorists from other countries. But I can't do it. But they didn't even do that with antifa. Or antifa. You know, two dozen people died in the George Floyd riots. They didn't get their panties in a bunch over that. But now they're doing it. Basically, nobody has -- nobody has broken a law, except honking. And then you got a C -- a bona fide CNN analyst threatening actual violence, basically trying to initiate violence by saying slash their tires, drain their gas tanks, blah, blah, blah. Imagine if they did that. That would actually initiate violence. That is an actual CN analyst trying to start something. Imagine if I said that about BLM-ers. Man. But the thing is, Canadian truckers, easy target, there's no thumbs up emoji for them. You know? But then she backtracked and said she was trying to talk about peaceful protests. No, she is an advocate for attacking a peaceful protest. CNN, again, wrong side of history, wrong side on everything. It's amazing.

utterances.speaker: JEANINE PIRRO, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: Isn't that incitement? You know, go --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Go slice their tires. You know, the amazing thing about thing about this is that Canada isn't used to this. The Canadians do not protest on the level of the United States.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: And to get these truckers who gave everything at a time when they didn't know how dangerous COVID was -- to make them into terrorists and insurrectionist is absolutely absurd. But what is so hypocritical -- and I'm so tired of using that word -- is for Biden to call up Trudeau and say look, you better make sure you stop them. Trudeau didn't even want to talk to them. He might have been able to stop some of this, but right now, they are now starting a protest on foot in Jericho, they're calling it the Jericho protest, they're protesting around parliament. And the truth is that, they are going to continue, because the world supports them. And when Trudeau was talking about foreign money, he's talking about money from the United States, money from all over the world. And any government that threatens to take money from people who give it for someone else is committing a crime, it's a fraud, it's larceny.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Geraldo, I think the only answer we put a wall up on the northern border and we just end this. Right?

utterances.speaker: GERALDO RIVERA, FOX NEWS CORRESPONDENT-AT-LARGE
utterances.sentences: Who -- whoever would have thought that the southern border would be less chaotic than the northern border? I think I have heard a lot of well-expressed but bogus analysis of what's happened.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Bogus analysis?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Yes, bogus analysis. I just got off the phone with my friend who lives in Toronto but does business in Ottawa. He says that Canadians are -- you know, they are nice people.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: They are.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: But they are -- they don't overreact. They are grotesquely annoyed or profoundly annoyed, I should say, that the government has taken this long to clean up the streets of the capital city. Calling them truckers is very romanticizing them. They are more like occupy Wall Street. Less than half of them are actually in the trucking business.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I mean, occupy Wall Street, they didn't have a job, what would you call them?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: There's a couple of --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: These people are truckers.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: There's a couple of thousand -- some are, half of them are. The other half are --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Who support them.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: -- occupy Wall Street types.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: No, they support the truckers. These are hardworking people.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: These are --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: These are the --

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: These are disgruntled people. Listen, they have a -- whatever their beef is, I understand that. I have no problem with people acting out to resolve issues that they have. What I have a problem with is when you stop trade between two nations, you put people out of work, you cause enormous --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Only the government can do that!

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Who put people out of work? The government put people out of work!

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Because Toyota and Ford are closing shifts now because they can't get parts because of the protests.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: No, but they voluntarily open one lane on their own. They don't want to stop it --

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: The pathetic thing about this is, the pathetic about this is that it has been allowed to go on for over two weeks. Can you imagine in the capital city, closing things down, annoying people to beat the ban and --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: They should set fire -- you know what, Geraldo, they should set fire at buildings. They did that all summer. I didn't hear you this passionate.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Where do you think -- where do you think they go to the bathroom? I'm just curious. Where do you think they go to the bathrooms?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Bathrooms.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: In those cans. In those cans.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Truckers know how to do that.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: In those cans lined up.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: All right, Dagen.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: By the way, I love how you, when it comes to lockdowns and masks, hey, don't stop, just a little bit longer, just a little bit, we're almost there, we're almost there.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: We're almost there.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Truckers show up and you go, my God, they are shutting things down. That has to stop right now.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: They are shutting down interstate commerce!

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: That's hypocritical.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: International commerce.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: You are talking about two sides of your mouth.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: That's an act of war. I am not.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: You wouldn't see two sides of my mouth.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: All right. Dagen McDowell.

utterances.speaker: DAGEN MCDOWELL, FOX NEWS BUSINESS CORRESPONDENT
utterances.sentences: To call closing some lanes on a bridge an act of war is the height of idiocy. There's some shifts that have been shut down and plants. And by the way, there are other bridges that go from Canada into the United States and back, so this is not a massive hardship. It doesn't help the case of the truckers that if your -- that if people are out of some hours on the job at a Ford plant or another plant, so they might want to think about that.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: True.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: But the very way that these leaders and these gassy clutter bags on CNN have handled this and talk about this, exemplifies why the truckers are protesting and angry in the first place. From the leaders, from Trudeau on down, bear edicts and decrease from on high, these would be emperors and kings -- they get treated as if they're like plebes and trolls over and over again. That it's beneath Trudeau to even sit down and talk to them. They don't deserve to be heard, they just -- they don't deserve a conversation. Just vilification from these leaders in Canada and these individuals on CNN. One thing about that CNN thing. She said take their gas, slash their tires, and then move the trucks -- does that moron not know how trucks actually operate? That if they don't have gas and their tires are flat, they're not moving anywhere?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Can I --

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: Just one more thing. These are the people who moved food --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: -- and necessities to all of us.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Some of them were.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Some of them.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: A lot of them were not.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Can I -- can I --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: They -- all the necessities.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: They were -- one thing, my friend in Ontario said that they are generally regarded as --

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: Is he a truck driver? Because if he is not, you can stick a sock in it.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: They are generally regarded as ultra-right ruffian.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: There you go. I want to agree with Geraldo. This blocking this bridge is wrong, because how is Justin Trudeau going to get his shoe polish?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes, that's right.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: He's got to put the blackface on.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes. And by the way --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Go ahead.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: He can't call anybody racist.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: One of the things they are objecting to is the term -- they want to terminate the digital tracking and the contract -- a contact tracing, which they are doing on your iPhone. You may want to look at it. You haven't agreed to it, but go through your settings that you bring trace.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: They're tracking?

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: If you bought a loaf of bread or some --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: -- Advil for your aching back because you were sitting on your ass all day long every day for two years, yes at CNN, you got it because of a trucker. Thank them, rather than sneering.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: OK. And I think we can all agree Geraldo's friend in Canada represents all of Canada.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: All of Canada.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Failing Biden can't take the heat. Joe snapping at a reporter, and we'll you next.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: And shock.

utterances.speaker: LESTER HOLT, ANCHOR, NBC
utterances.sentences: I think it was back in July, you said inflation was going to be temporary. I think a lot of Americans are wondering what your definition of temporary is.

utterances.speaker: JOE BIDEN, PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA
utterances.sentences: Well, I think you are being a wise guy with me a little bit. And I understand that's your job. According to a Nobel Laureate there's 14 of them that contacted me and a number of corporate leaders, it going to start to taper off as we go through this year.

utterances.speaker: BIDEN
utterances.sentences: It's hard to say whether they -- here is the science is saying now that masks work, masks make a difference, and there is a relation. I've -- I commit that I would follow the science. The science as put forward by the CDC and the federal people. I think it's probably premature, but it's a, you know, it's a tough call.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: But Judge, Nobel Laureates, 17 of them.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes. Yes, I wasn't down.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: What's there with 17?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I don't know.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: You know, you can't say Nobel Laureates when you are the president. You just can't use that phrase. No one knows what it is.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Nobody cares.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: And no one cares. People actually look down on Nobel Laureates. They gave Obama the Peace Prize before he even came into office, I think. And then if you listen to the rest of his answer, he says, you know what, well, we are going to build an Intel chip manufacturer in Ohio. I mean, that doesn't take weeks. That takes years. That's not going to do anything about gas or food. They got us -- don't have any answers.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: There's big news, big news in Ohio.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I do like the fact that he has a nickname for people. That's one thing I like about.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Wise guy.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I like wise guy, you know, lying dogface, pony soldier. I want to know what he calls Kamala. That's what I want to know. And then he says, you know what, it's premature to pull back on the masks. He doesn't know what premature is. He wants to spend trillions to change the weather 100 years from now. He doesn't know anything about what premature means.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: OK. So, I'll give that one to ou. Geraldo, is it premature to pull back on the masks for children, when the American Academy of Pediatrics says --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Are they Nobel Laureates?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: -- that all the states reporting 0.0 -- or 0.01 percent of all child COVID resulted in deaths.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Let me say that although I like him as a person, he is not nimble as a president.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Is he smart?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: I don't know if he is smart or not, I think that he must be.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Why?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: But he is having -- he's having a failure to communicate, to connect.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Why is he, why do you think he is smart?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Well, he's had a -- I don't want to go into his whole biography --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: I'm masking?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: -- and all the rest of it.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Is he smart today?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: He was vice president of the United States.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Is he smart today as president?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: He is not as -- when I say he's not nimble, what I mean is, he has lost the step in terms of his response.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: I know that.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Like sitting at this table, he would have a hard time with you, Toronto. But I do think that the governors, the Democratic governors are picking up the slack and may save -- may save the party from an absolute route, but I don't know if we are going to talk about Crime -- not Crimea - - about Ukraine. But we -- we could all be engaged in a war in Europe.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: C block.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Or the C block.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Geraldo.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: That's a smart --

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Well, we'll have to put -- we got to put a big cliffhanger.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Is he smart? But you didn't answer that question.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: I believe that he, I think that it is an irrelevant --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: It's a yes or no question.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: -- question and I don't know the answer.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: I don't know.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: That's because he doesn't want to answer it. Is he smart?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I think he might have been at some point in his life --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Today!

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: No. It's kind of sad. And also, he's not -- he's not telling the truth. That's probably the -- 14, do you actually believe 14 Nobel Laureates -- do you think they --

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Seventeen.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Seventeen, sorry, 17. Yes, it was 14 national security whatever. But 17.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: They contacted him.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: So, 17 contacted, they contacted him. That is -- that is easily checkable.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes. I'd like to speak to the president please.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Who am I? I'm a Nobel Laureate.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: OK. Here's my --

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Sorry.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Here's my theory.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: A robocall.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: You can't be concerned over woke-ism and virtue signaling, and crime, inflation and COVID. The hard left radical postures, that's been taking up his limited shelf space in his brain. Right? All that stuff that put in, pushed down, all the stuff that he supposed to care about. He is supposed to care about the real concerns of the American people, which to me right now obviously is crime and inflation. But he can't do it. Because there is an opportunity cost to the obsession with identity, and ironically, it's affecting the identities that the left claim to defend, right? It's minorities that are getting hit hardest with inflation. It's a systemic racist point, you know, the inflation. So, I mean, this is, we are watching the consequences of a man who is essentially a husk.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: And they filled it up with woke-ism, and he's just like, he's like a dead robot.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: A dead robot.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: He's a dead robot.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: That's --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: That's redundant.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: All right. You know what, Dagen, Dagen, what we have now is we've got people like Senator Mark Warner saying let's get rid of the gas tax and that will save Americans money. And now we also have Obama calling in to some of these Democrat political calls. What do you make of this?

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: That that's gasping for desperation because they can't lean on Joe Biden who is in cognitive decline. I don't understand. It's worse by the day and by the month. And he sat down with Lester Holt at a time -- Geraldo raised it, we are going to talk about it in the next block -- but Russia is on the verge of invading Ukraine. Why wouldn't he sit down -- and I know President Trump did not do live interviews on this, before the Super Bowl, but Joe Biden hasn't done a sit- down interview so far this year. This was his first. He did a taped interview days before it was going to air. Wouldn't he try to reassure the American people, and sit down and at least do same-day taping or even, if you believe that you were capable of doing an interview with Lester Holt, do it live on the day of the Super Bowl. What else does he got going on? He's got a mani-pedi pregame?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Well --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: He's going to Camp David.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: But I want to say one thing about, I know, but you get -- you can get mani-pedis at Camp David.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: You can get everything.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes, I know.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: So, they tell me, Jesse.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: I want to say really quickly one thing about inflation. Inflation, yes. It's at a 40-year high, but right now, it's much worse than 1982. Back then, a risk-averse responsible conservative saver could put their money in a CD or bank account and earn 8 to 10 percent on it. Right now, when you have your money in the bank, you are losing 7 percent every year. This Federal Reserve and this man in the White House running fiscal policy is -- they are promoting gambling. The only way that you can keep up with inflation with your money is by taking on downside risk of 20, 30, 40, or 50 percent.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes. All right.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.sentences: That's a horrific place to put hardworking Americans.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: All right. Coming up, the world bracing for a Russian invasion of Ukraine, but don't worry, Kamala Harris is on the job.

utterances.speaker: HOLT
utterances.sentences: What scenarios would you put American troops to rescue and get Americans out?

utterances.speaker: BIDEN
utterances.sentences: There's not. That's a world war. When Americans and Russians start shooting at one another. I'm hoping that if in fact, he is foolish enough to go in, he's smart enough not to, in fact, do anything that would negatively impact on American citizens. American citizens should leave, should leave now. We are dealing with one of the largest armies in the world. It's a very different situation and things can go crazy quickly.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Well, what's interesting about this is, and disappointing, is that he doesn't imagine a scenario where he's going to go in and protect Americans if we are in a situation where Russia invades.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: I agree with that.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: I mean, he did it, he did it in Afghanistan, although he lied initially, he said we are going to protect the Americans, we'll take care of them, we'll get them out. And then he said, no, we are not going to them out. Now he's saying ahead of time we are not going to get Americans out. That is disgusting that alone should be enough. You want to talk impeachment? That should be impeachment? But the issue of the Ukraine is very interesting. Because I spoke to someone today and he said to me. Look, he said the Russians have about 120,000 troops on the borders, they've got about 100,000 in Belarus doing training. He says, but the Russian economy is so bad that the thought of them actually invading and actually staying there doesn't make sense, because they can't afford to keep the troops there. Plus, since they already have access to the water in the Eastern Ukraine, they're already there, they really don't have to go in there. If they go into Kiev, the Ukrainians are tough fighters, and they're going to give them a real run for their money. So, I'm not so sure it's imminent.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: But the problem -- that the reason it could be imminent, Jesse, is that just think of all those tanks parked there running the engines the whole time. Think about the soldiers have to eat. They got to have heat, they get they get sick. I mean, to maintain a force of that size in the field is enormously expensive. He can't keep them there forever. It's use them or lose them.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: But it's even more expensive once they go in with the supply lines and all the fuel and everything like that.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA

utterances.utterance: That that's gasping for desperation because they can't lean on Joe Biden who is in cognitive decline. I don't understand. It's worse by the day and by the month. And he sat down with Lester Holt at a time -- Geraldo raised it, we are going to talk about it in the next block -- but Russia is on the verge of invading Ukraine. Why wouldn't he sit down -- and I know President Trump did not do live interviews on this, before the Super Bowl, but Joe Biden hasn't done a sit- down interview so far this year. This was his first. He did a taped interview days before it was going to air. Wouldn't he try to reassure the American people, and sit down and at least do same-day taping or even, if you believe that you were capable of doing an interview with Lester Holt, do it live on the day of the Super Bowl. What else does he got going on? He's got a mani-pedi pregame?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Well --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: He's going to Camp David.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: But I want to say one thing about, I know, but you get -- you can get mani-pedis at Camp David.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You can get everything.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Yes, I know.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: So, they tell me, Jesse.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: I want to say really quickly one thing about inflation. Inflation, yes. It's at a 40-year high, but right now, it's much worse than 1982. Back then, a risk-averse responsible conservative saver could put their money in a CD or bank account and earn 8 to 10 percent on it. Right now, when you have your money in the bank, you are losing 7 percent every year. This Federal Reserve and this man in the White House running fiscal policy is -- they are promoting gambling. The only way that you can keep up with inflation with your money is by taking on downside risk of 20, 30, 40, or 50 percent.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Yes. All right.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: That's a horrific place to put hardworking Americans.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: All right. Coming up, the world bracing for a Russian invasion of Ukraine, but don't worry, Kamala Harris is on the job.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA (on camera)
utterances.utterance: The Biden administration urgently warning this afternoon about the imminent outbreak of war in Europe. President Biden will be speaking to Putin tomorrow. The White House saying forcefully that, quote, "we are in the window of a possible Russian invasion of Ukraine," which, quote, "could begin during the Olympics." That is before or after February the 20th. That's next Friday. President Biden warning Americans to get out of Ukraine while they still can.

utterances.speaker: HOLT
utterances.utterance: What scenarios would you put American troops to rescue and get Americans out?

utterances.speaker: BIDEN
utterances.utterance: There's not. That's a world war. When Americans and Russians start shooting at one another. I'm hoping that if in fact, he is foolish enough to go in, he's smart enough not to, in fact, do anything that would negatively impact on American citizens. American citizens should leave, should leave now. We are dealing with one of the largest armies in the world. It's a very different situation and things can go crazy quickly.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA (on camera)
utterances.utterance: All right. With the threat of war very -- I got my dates mixed up there but very (Inaudible) of this next Sunday. With the threat of war very real in Europe, the president turning to a national security rookie, with all due respect, Vice President Kamala Harris. Not a lot of experience on the international scene, to try to resolve his urgent crisis despite her failure so far with the issues like our southern border. The vice president will be headed to Germany next week to rally allies against Russia. This is for real, Judge. I don't know why they're so -- the warnings are so urgent, but they seem to have a real edge, they seemed to really sound, to me, like they are very forceful and imminent is the word that comes to my mind.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Well, what's interesting about this is, and disappointing, is that he doesn't imagine a scenario where he's going to go in and protect Americans if we are in a situation where Russia invades.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: I agree with that.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: I mean, he did it, he did it in Afghanistan, although he lied initially, he said we are going to protect the Americans, we'll take care of them, we'll get them out. And then he said, no, we are not going to them out. Now he's saying ahead of time we are not going to get Americans out. That is disgusting that alone should be enough. You want to talk impeachment? That should be impeachment? But the issue of the Ukraine is very interesting. Because I spoke to someone today and he said to me. Look, he said the Russians have about 120,000 troops on the borders, they've got about 100,000 in Belarus doing training. He says, but the Russian economy is so bad that the thought of them actually invading and actually staying there doesn't make sense, because they can't afford to keep the troops there. Plus, since they already have access to the water in the Eastern Ukraine, they're already there, they really don't have to go in there. If they go into Kiev, the Ukrainians are tough fighters, and they're going to give them a real run for their money. So, I'm not so sure it's imminent.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: But the problem -- that the reason it could be imminent, Jesse, is that just think of all those tanks parked there running the engines the whole time. Think about the soldiers have to eat. They got to have heat, they get they get sick. I mean, to maintain a force of that size in the field is enormously expensive. He can't keep them there forever. It's use them or lose them.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: But it's even more expensive once they go in with the supply lines and all the fuel and everything like that.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: And Ukrainian shooting at them from afar.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: So, you know, I used to think he wasn't going in and now I think he might just take half of the country and not even try for Kiev. But what do I know? I have no idea what he's going to do. But if he does go in, he's going to bleed to death in that country. My God, I don't think that's going to go very well for Putin. I just imagine what would happen if Trump were President right now and how the mind would be covering this. Trump has allowed Vlad to gobble up Ukraine in exchange for his help for beating Hillary Clinton in the election. Donald Trump vacationing in, you know, three-day weekend at Camp David while Americans are left stranded there, as NATO crumbles while Trump golfs. You know, and he sends Mike Pence so he doesn't have to go there. I mean, come on, Geraldo.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: And what about Kamala? What about Kamala.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Yes, what about her?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Kamala? Listen, I would have sent Hunter. Hunter knows everything in that trade. But you can look at it this way. She's been begging for a better role. You know what, hey, this is the big leagues, babe. This is high stakes diplomacy. You wanted something big, you wanted to go to Europe, go for it. Let's see how it shakes out. In other hand, you're basically giving her a really tough thing and she could come back with Russia already invaded Ukraine and Germany saying, you know what, we're not going to close Nord Stream 2, and that could look even worse.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: You can't -- and Judge -- I wanted to mention, before I went to Jesse, that they can't rescue Americans in Ukraine when the Russians are occupying. You can't put American forces and Russian forces in the same neighborhood.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Yes, because then they'll start fighting, obviously.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: It would be -- it would be a European war.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: It would be war. It would war.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: But Dagen, one of the positive things that the President has accomplished is Putin is now facing a united NATO more or less. The NATO was shattered, remember? The United States was half-assed participating. There were countries that didn't know whether joining NATO is a good idea after all. You know, the one thing that Putin is manages to unite NATO again.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: We'll see.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Well, we'll see. Where are the sanctions then? Why aren't we being proactive rather than reactive? If you go in, we're going to lay sanctions on them. There's so much --

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: So, you would do it right now?

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: We should have done it weeks ago, we should have taken -- you know, United Kingdom can start cracking down on the personal assets of Putin and his cronies, because most of them or a lot of them are housed in London or in England, number one. There's so much that we could have done. Why -- Nord Stream 2, why wait for that? That's number one. Number two, I said this a year ago, or over a year ago, on this very show. Biden dismantling our energy economy and destroying our strength on the world stage where we were the swing producer, we controlled world prices, we had the most excess production capacity, we were the number one energy producer in the world. Biden destroyed that and handed power control and wealth to Russia and Iran, nations that want to wipe us off the planet. You saw today oils at $94 a barrel. Then he turns around and starts begging OPEC to pump more oil in August. So, not only did we enrich Russia, Russia is in a much better economic place now because oil is at a seven-year, eight-year high. But we also emboldened Putin because weakness is the oxygen of tyrants.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: What about on the political front, Greg? If Biden were to announce, to Dagen's point, we are -- I made a mistake. He didn't have -- he doesn't have to apologise. I'm reopening on an emergency -- national emergency basis. The Keystone Pipeline, the XL Pipeline, every other damn pipeline they shut down, every refinery that put on hold.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Well, that wasn't built yet. That wasn't built yet. They should open up all land leases. They should just say pumped to the sky.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: What -- would that help -- would that save him and us?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Maybe, but I don't think -- I don't know if that's the issue right now. I'm happy that Kamala is going to the Ukraine to explore the root causes of the Russian border problem. She's probably going to get the history, would come back and report -- do a nice little book report. I also love that fact that Biden has brought us firmly back into the 1970s. We got the 1970s crime rates. We got the 1970s gas prices. Now, it looks like we're going to have a 1970s proxy war with an evil empire. I was looking for -- if he continues that, he is going to resurrect the Manson family, and that's going to be really interesting. Where's Jim Jones? He's going to bring back everything bad about it. But you first --

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: My platform shoes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes. Geraldo is here.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Oh, yes. First, you got to ask though, how does this Intel on the Ukraine compared to the Intel in Afghanistan, right? We should ask ourselves that. And we brought up NATO. If Putin doesn't want the Ukraine in NATO, why do we care? This is -- this is confusing me. Reverse history and consider an independent Texas joining the Warsaw Pact, all right. We could say like oh, we -- NATO this, NATO that, it's really important. It really isn't that important. What do we get out of this? We get nothing out of this. Then, put it in human terms, yes, Russia -- Putin is a bully and the Ukraine are the bullied and America is always on the side of the bullied, which means we should help the Ukraine. We should --

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: What should we do?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Well, if we go -- we have supply arms, we have to -- my feeling is that's not going to happen.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: So, you wouldn't put the 82nd Airborne in?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Hell, no.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: Good.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What's good is that for us?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: What good is that for us? Well, amen. And that we agree. I just got a note quickly from Canada --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Is this from Ontario?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: From Ontario. The Teamsters -- the Teamsters are saying to the protesters go home, go home. We join in the calls urging the protest with legitimate concern --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Oh, please.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Who controls Canada, the Teamsters or Trudeau?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: You know what, I could get -- I could get the same from someone else.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: "THE FASTEST" is up next.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Welcome back. Time for "THE FASTEST." The judge was criticising my music.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: I don't know what (INAUDIBLE).

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: What are -- what are we getting ready for the big Super Bowl showdown this Sunday? 100 million Americans will be watching as the Bengals face off against the Rams. But what can be more important than the game? The food. We've assembled a killer spread thanks to Morgan's Brooklyn Barbecue. Greg has devoured a good chunk of it.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I'm on my fourth rib, and that was just during the break.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Hand me the rubber gloves. I just have to show you. Greg, I'm apparently carries around in your briefcase --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: -- collection of rubber gloves in case he has to eat ribs.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No, no, no, no, that's wet wipes inside the rubber glove.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: OK.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: Rob Cartier (PH).

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's for a barbecue and in case I go to prison.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: If I was wearing a hat, I'd tip it to you, sir.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Thank you.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Jesse, what are you doing for the game?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I'll just watch it at home. I don't really care who wins. No one cares who wins. This is like the least anticipated Super Bowl that I could remember. There's no real stars, quarterback. They're too young quarterbacks. No one that doesn't follow football knows anything about the Super Bowl. But you know, hopefully, since he comes from behind and wins at the end.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Geraldo, what are you doing?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: I'm having two parties. I have a party Saturday and a party Sunday, I've been informed. Sunday is a very eclectic group, both catering from Doug Katz and also some finger food like this.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Thanks for the invite, by the way.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: You're always invited Greg, despite your severely attitude.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You better order --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I'm not invited to any party because I don't go.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Yes, they don't -- you don't get the invite because you won't show up.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: Yes, that's the problem.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Judge, what are you doing?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Nothing. Nothing, but I'll have the game on because I want to -- I want to see the commercials.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Oh, God.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: What?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I can't watch games like that.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: That's women.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Because you guys are loud during game, and then during the commercials, you're like, everybody, quiet.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: Oh, was that sexist?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's so funny.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Yes, well, I'm with my dogs. Nobody cares, OK. It's just me and the dogs.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: Her dogs are so pretty.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: I like the commercials. I want to see the halftime show.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Who's performing?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Eminem.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Dr. Dre, Snoop Dogg, Eminem.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes, you like those song?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: I do.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: Kendrick Lamar who doesn't like --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Name A Dr. Dre song.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: I could name an Eminem song.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Which one?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Monster under my bed or something.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: But I see you rocking with Eminem.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Wait. before you take a bite of that brisket there, Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: What are you doing this weekend?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I'm watching all of the Tyrus and Timpf podcasts because they claim that they trashed me in every single one and I've never really listened to them. So, instead of watching the Super Bowl, I'm going to do that.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: Why are you hungry?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You're not watching the Super Bowl?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: Why are you so hungry?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: This is my dinner.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: And you are -- you always see in front of millions of --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I don't care. I mean, this is what I do.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: It's delicious.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: When I get free food for Morgan's I'm eating it, because you know what? I gotta leave and then where does this food go?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Just relax.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: Put it in your baggie.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No, this is my rubber glove.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: You're supposed to -- if there's food on set, you're supposed to eat it.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: So, I'll have -- this is a deep-fried Oreo. Here we go.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Wait, who do you got? You're not -- you don't care?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I don't even know who's playing.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Bengals? Who has the Bengals?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: You know, I love hammer. We love we love hammer.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: We love Hammer. It's all about the Bengals.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: And you know, Cleveland to beat for Cincinnati, you got to really be very young down low.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Young down low?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Don't go anywhere.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Yes. We'll be right back. "FAN MAIL FRIDAY" is up next.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, it's great. I don't feel well because I just eat too fast. I eat too fast. I understand.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: That's why you're always burping.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I know. "FAN MAIL FRIDAY." First one. What is your most memorable athletic feat? All right, Geraldo let's get yours out of the way.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: I used to box for charity for my developmentally disabled charity. The charity is them to benefit. And fight the Wall Street champion that they put up, whoever bid the most, to fight me. And I was I was a bad boxer. They were much better boxers but I had staying power and I won the big match at Madison Square Garden.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Nice.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: You're fantastic.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Judge?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: This is embarrassing, but it is my most memorable feat. The first time I went to SoulCycle which was like eight years ago, whenever, nine years ago. So, I go into a dark room, my girlfriend says you got to come, you got to come. So, I get on the bicycle -- I never been to SoulCycle my life. I didn't know what it was like. I thought everybody was nuts. They were in the dark. And they kept going like this, right? Like, you bend your elbows and you know -- so I'm looking at everybody and go like this. I chipped my front tooth on the bar of the bicycle. And I --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You should have sued.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: That's what I did.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: Is that the one you spit out on your show?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: No, it's probably the same tooth. I just sued that dentist.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You spit out that does you spit out a tooth on your show?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Oh, yes, I was fighting with someone.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: I caught the tooth. She kept --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: She caught the --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You have to get a tape of that.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: Oh, yes. I have it. I have the tape.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Producers.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: We should. That's" ONE MORE THING." Montana, do that.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: All right, Dagen.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: I used to mountain bike. I was not good at anything athletic, any physical activity -- well, nevermind.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Dagen.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: And I would -- and I would -- I learned to a mountain bike when I was living in Colorado and I used to mountain bike in Moab, Utah. And I could whip some man butt.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes?

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: I was proud of that, yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What about you?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Fifth grade, in the gym./

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Basketball.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Very good.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Tie game, 10 seconds left, I steal the ball, go down the court, winning lay-up at the buzzer and my grandmother was watching.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oh, fantastic.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: And you had one with your daughter too.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Highlight of my athletic career right there. It's great. I peaked, I think.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: I think your daughter dunked it.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I landed a free throw in third grade basketball. It was the only time I ever scored in my life. It's kind of sad when you think about it. One more?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: I'm the only one with a bad physical experience.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What is your favourite errand on your day off? Dagen?

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: Buying Red Bull and a big bag of kettle corn at CVS.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Jesse?

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: In the morning.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's amazing.

utterances.speaker: MCDOWELL
utterances.utterance: I go to the flower shop.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oh, please.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: Oh, what a brat.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I think I'm going to throw up.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: I like that.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Now you're going to make me throw up.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: That's nice.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: This food is fantastic. Geraldo?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: I'm just walking around with the dogs. I like -- I like me and the dogs communicate and down to the creek.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That's not an errand, Geraldo.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.utterance: It's not quite an errand but it is a bit --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You don't take your Bentley in for a little tune up?
